│ THOUGHT: The crash occurs because InstCombine folds a shuffle into a select when the shuffle widens the vector length, causing a mismatch between the select condition vector length and │
│ the result vector length. Select requires the condition vector length to match the result vector length. Therefore, we should guard FoldOpIntoSelect to only trigger when the select's   │
│ condition vector element count equals the shufflevector result element count. This preserves same-length folds (keeping tests passing) while preventing the widening-case crash.         │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -i '2905,2911c\      if (auto *SVVT = dyn_cast<VectorType>(SVI.getType())) {\n        if (auto *CondVT = dyn_cast<VectorType>(SI->getCondition()->getType())) {\n          if        │
│ (SVVT->getElementCount() == CondVT->getElementCount()) {\n            if (Instruction *I = FoldOpIntoSelect(SVI, SI))\n              return I;\n          }\n        }\n      }'         │
│ llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineVectorOps.cpp && nl -ba llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineVectorOps.cpp | sed -n '2902,2914p'                                        │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
