│ THOUGHT: The crash occurs when InstCombine folds a widen shufflevector into a select, causing SelectInst::Create to assert because the select’s result type and condition vector length  │
│ don’t match. The most robust fix is to add a guard in FoldOpIntoSelect itself to ensure we only create a SelectInst when the select result type equals the folded op’s type and, for     │
│ vector types, the condition vector length matches the result vector length. This prevents invalid SelectInst creation across all callers, including the shufflevector fold. I will       │
│ modify InstructionCombining.cpp to add these checks right before creating the SelectInst, then run the InstCombine tests.                                                                │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
